The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                The Assembly plunged into darkness for 15 minutes on Wednesday afternoon following a fault at CESCs 6KV feeder supplying power to the building. All India Radio and the treasury buildings were also affected. The discussion on agriculture budget had just started in the Assembly when the lights went out and emergency lights were switched on. Deputy Speaker Bhaktipada Ghosh adjourned the House till 2 pm. Trinamul Congress MLAs shouted slogans in the lobby, protesting power cuts.     Television actor Saptarshi Roy was arrested on Wednesday night after his wife Payal lodged a complaint against him, alleging physical and mental harassment and criminal breach of trust. Cops said Saptarshi had forced Payal to get money from her parents after their marriage in 2007.     The West Bengal Council of Higher Education on Wednesday set up a committee to implement the University Grant Commissions recent decision making it mandatory for PhD and MPhil degree holders to clear the NET or the SLET to teach in colleges and universities.     Amit Pal, 54, died on Wednesday after his motorcycle was dashed by a private bus plying on route 21/1 on Tollygunge Circular Road on Wednesday. He was taken to SSKM hospital. The driver fled.                                                                                                                                                                
